1.9.1 (June 23, 2026)
  Switch to Java 21.
1.9.0 (April 14, 2026)
  Integration of resolution/superposition prover by Viktoria Langenreither.
1.8.5 (February 20, 2026)
  Minor bug fix to allow reading problem file also in case of option "-web".
1.8.4 (February 25, 2025)
  Minor bug fix in transforming choose expressions and problem decomposition.
1.8.3 (December 11, 2024)
  Minor bug fixes related to problem decomposition and formula display.
1.8.2 (November 27, 2024)
  Minor bug fixes related to problem decomposition and proof display.
1.8.1 (July 22, 2024)
  Minor changes and bug fixes related to problem decomposition.
1.8.0 (July 15, 2024)
  Numerous improvements and bug fixes in MESON proving and SMT solving.
1.7.1 (November 23, 2023)
  Improvements and bug fixes in GUI and equality/theory reasoning.
1.7.0 (October 12, 2023)
  Equality reasoning in paramodulation-like style.
1.6.0 (September 23, 2023)
  Theory support for MESON prover by axiomatization and/or SMT solving.
  Experimental support for Stefan Ratschan's ExSpec solver.
1.5.2 (June 22, 2023)
  Switch to Java 17.  
1.5.1 (June 13, 2023)
  Improved memory handling for large proof search trees.
1.5.0 (June 12, 2023)
  Introduce model elimination (MESON) prover.
1.4.3 (March 23, 2023)
  Initial code for model elimination prover.
1.4.2 (March 8, 2023)
  Introduce a low-overhead term representation for first-order proof methods.
1.4.1 (March 2, 2023)
  Introduce clausal form computation.
  Prepare for first-order proof methods 'me' and 'res'.
1.4 (February 22, 2023)
  Introduce problem decomposition and web GUI.
1.3.1 (September 16, 2022)
  Fix bug in map store axiom.
1.3 (July 22, 2013)
  Introduce "choose[sat]" expressions.
1.2 (July 8, 2022)
  Integrate bindings for cvc5 and Vampire.
1.1 (July 6, 2022)
  First version used in RISCAL with various bug fixes
  and (mostly internal) changes, in particular: 
  - internal reorganization to make library thread-safe.
  - remove constraint that applications of the tuple constructor
    must be syntactically preceded by the tuple type.
  - if SMT solver yields "sat", print counterexample model (only
    the values of integer constants) 
1.0 (June 8, 2022)
  First release.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
End of CHANGES.
